<HL>
   Technology:
   Merck Opens a Lab in Italy
</HL>
<DATE>
05/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   MRK EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   RAHWAY, N.J. -- Merck &amp; Co., a health products company,
said it opened a research laboratory in Pomezia, Italy, near
Rome, to undertake research in human diseases such as cancer
and viral infections.
   The Instituto di Ricerche di Biologia Molecolare, a joint
venture for research in Italy, was formed by an Italian
subsidiary of Merck and Sigma Tau Industrie Farmaceutiche
Riunite S.p.A., an Italian pharmaceutical company. The $50
million facility will employ approximately 100 researchers
and nonscientific personnel.
